{"key":"processedPost-12448424","value":{"id":12448424,"first":12442991,"last":12462315,"when":1272123310,"utime":"04/24/10 06:35 PM","content":"Autoclaves are generally not suitable for our purposes.&nbsp; Most autoclaves are set up to dump pressure at the end of the cycle.&nbsp; This results in a massive and sudden loss of pressure, which also takes ALL of the moisture out too.&nbsp; This is great for the CIA torture facilities. . .Oops, I meant instruments that dentists commonly use, but will ruin the moisture content of your jars.<br /><br />We use pressure cookers, not autoclaves for mushroom grains and substrates.&nbsp; If you don't have a regular pressure cooker that will cool slowly and remain sealed, you'll want to stick to the brf tek where you can sterilize in a large pot with a tight fitting lid.<br />RR","title":"Re: autoclaving?"}}